          <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="beeches"></a>Purley Beeches work party Saturday, 4th June, 23rd July</h3>
                <p>Wow! What a success our last work party was, fifteen adults and four children turned out to help. Obviously the lure of a good bonfire promised an easy time, but not so, everybody including the children worked really hard to cut and drag more material to the fire.</p>

                <p>Now it’s back to the regular stuff. It’s time to start clearing the spring growth around our newly planted saplings and to help with this the FOPB has bought a couple of sickles, but only to be used by experienced persons. More path widening and of course, continuing to press on into our new site, which looks bigger each time I visit. Removing dead wood and the thick undergrowth is the order of the day. Fortunately the ground has hardened which will make access to and from the site easier. I think most people now know where the site is, so it would make sense for the early birds to go directly there rather than waiting at the gate.</p>

                <p>The usual request for hand tools and appropriate gloves, shoes and clothing apply. We will keep to the revised time of 10am to 1pm and the next two work party dates follow, June 4th and July 23rd</p>
                <p>For further information please email or call Stanley Lowy: 020 8657 3684 or <%= mail_to "stanlowy@outlook.com" %>, Elizabeth Bennett: <%= mail_to "bennett_e@sky.com" %>, Mac Court   <%= mail_to "mac@skyy.me.uk" %></p>
              </td>
              <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/purley_beeches100.jpg", alt: "Purley Beeches logo"), "/resource/purley_beeches_enrol.pdf" %>
              </td>
            </tr>


          <tr>
            <td class="events">
              <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="hearme"></a>Hear Me Speak, debating competition for Primary Schools. Thursday 9th June, 3.15 - 4 pm</h3>
              <p>The third year of our popular debating competition for year 6 children is to be held at Hamsey Green Primary School. For more information please contact Cliff Quartly <%= mail_to "francisquartly@hotmail.co.uk" %></p>
            </td>
            <td class="events"><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/residents_logo100.jpg", alt: "SRA logo"), "http://www.sanderstead-residents.co.uk" %>
