          <tr>
            <td class="events">
               <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="gruffy"></a>16th Purley Scouts’ 45th Gruffy Fayre, Saturday 11th June 2016 12 - 5 pm</h3>
               <p>The Gruffy Fayre returns this year on the 11th June from 12 pm. From its humble beginnings in 1971, the Fayre has grown into a much anticipated annual community event held on the Gruffy (next to Sanderstead Pond) offering fun for all the family.  This year is no exception, with what promises to be an even bigger and better array of entertainment to exhaust your little (and not so little) ones! Rodeo Ball, Laser Tag, Bouncy Castles, Slides and Human Hungry Hippos to name but a few!  And for the less energetic; tombolas, raffles with fantastic prizes and lots of traditional side shows to occupy your time.  There is even space to kick back and enjoy some time out, with refreshments on offer, including tea and home baked cakes, our ever popular BBQ and Pimms to enjoy in the Summer sunshine.  And let’s not forget the opportunity to cheer onour local Cubs as the inter pack football tournament runs throughout the day   Forget the Euro’s, the Gruffy is where it’s at this Summer with the kick off whistle being blown by our local MP Chris Philp.</p>  
              <p>All the fun of the Fayre helps to ensure that the 16th Purley Scout Group can continue to offer wonderful Scouting experiences to our local children, including Beaver Sleepovers, fun days and Summer Camps as well as funding maintenance for their ageing Scout Hut. So why not come along and join the throng on 11th June, and pick up a Prize Programme (on sale at Waitrose Sanderstead Saturday 4th June) for an opportunity to win some wonderful prizes!</p>
            </td>
             <td class="events">
              <h3><%= link_to("Gruffy Fayre", "/resource/Gruffy2016.pdf") %></h3>
            </td>
          </tr>

